@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'DoorMaze' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, your Workbench must have at least
8 colours.

                             How to play?

  Gameplay is simple: click on a 'door', represented by a vertical
or horizontal bar, that is located at the uppper, lower, right or
left space, next to your position (which is indicated by a smiling
face icon). Clicking on the other doors, diamond-shaped tiles
between doors or brick walls will have no effect. Note that you can
use the cursor keys to move in the game area.

  When you click on a normal door, or on a coloured door and a key
of the same colour has been found, the smiling face icon will move
towards the space located on the other side. The game display will
then be updated and your position will be located at the center of
the displayed area.

  When you see a coloured key, just go over it to pick it up. That
key will then appear in the rectangular box located at the right of
the displayed game area.

  You can restart a game anytime by clicking on the 'New Game'
button.

  To quit the game, click on the game window's closebutton or press
the 'Esc' key.

  Have fun!

@endnode

